In this section, rather than providing a comprehensive description of the numerical
methods used here for the space and time discretization of the various models of ﬂuid
surfaces, we outline a few key elements in our numerical treatment of ﬂuid surfaces.
First, we introduce a variational time integrator based on Onsager’ s principle, which is
unconditionally stable by construction. Then, we summarize the spatial discretization
of the different ﬁelds on the time-ev olving surface. We end with the deri vation of
the discrete equations for an inextensible ﬂuid surface with bending elasticity as a
reference example.
